  "title": "Texas Lost a Giraffe Named Gracie",
  "script": "Texas lost a giraffe! Cedar Hollow Ranch in Real County had a problem Monday: Gracie — their giraffe — wandered to a corner of the property the herd never visits, found a gate, and walked out. Into the Texas Hill Country. By herself. The ranch offered a $5,000 reward. Authorities asked the public for help. A game camera caught her west of Leakey — which, if you're wondering, is deep in the Texas Hill Country. Ranch manager Vick Jones says she's been located and he's hoping to get her back Tuesday. The question nobody's asking: how does a giraffe just disappear? She's 15 feet tall. You can see her from a mile away. How does a 15-foot animal just vanish?",
